title: Goat Island | New Zealand
tags: ['NZ', 'nature', 'summer', 'holiday', '4k', 'gopro', 'snapper', 'marine', 'marine reserve', 'wildlife', 'backyard', 'fish', 'goat island', 'diving', 'snorkling', 'HD']
description:
Swimming with fish was rad need to do it again when it is warmer for sure! Here's some fun facts about the island:

Goat Island is named after the goats released by early European seafarers, to provide food for those who became marooned. In 1975 the waters around the island were made New Zealand’s first marine reserve, Cape Rodney–Ōkakari Point Marine Reserve. Since then it has been used for fisheries research and as a training ground for recreational divers.


And this specific 'Goat' island has apparently never had any goats on it lol

title: To a good friend.
description:
Going on a feel trip bois. (Hardest video I have ever filmed and edited)

It is a sad event that happened. I am still in shock like many of his family, friends, work mates etc are. This is my weird way of dealing with it through a creative outlet. description:
The horror that unfolded last Friday was unbelievable and still is. I am still shocked at how this can happen in our NZ (And still am). I didnt want to make the usual vlog as this event had been on my mind and I cant stop thinking about it, instead I decided to make a memorial video to show how amazing our New Zealand is. 
We can band together is such a short amount of time with so much support and love. I am truly amazed at how much support there is from all over the nation and around the world. 
This has made stronger as we band together as one. We Are One.

My deepest condolences for Muslim community and for the families and friends lost on March 15th 2019.
#ThisIsNotUs

Thank you for The Herald in allowing me use some of their footage and images all sources can be found on their page https://www.nzherald.co.nz/
